\subsection{Validation Data}

\subsubsection{JRC Global Surface Water (GSW)}
The JRC Global Surface Water dataset \citep{pekel2016} provides long-term (1984--2021) monthly water classification history derived from Landsat imagery at 30~m resolution. Monthly water history products (\texttt{JRC/GSW1\_4/MonthlyHistory}) were used as the primary independent reference for accuracy assessment.

\subsubsection{High-Resolution Optical Imagery}
Google Earth Pro imagery and Sentinel-2 composites were used for qualitative visual validation at selected locations across different land cover types.

\subsection{Administrative Boundaries}
FAO GAUL Level-1 (divisions) and Level-2 (districts) boundary datasets, accessed through Google Earth Engine, were used for spatial aggregation and multi-scale reporting.

\subsection{Processing Platform}
All SAR data processing, water detection, and product generation were performed in Google Earth Engine (GEE) \citep{gorelick2017}, enabling cloud-based access to the complete Sentinel-1 archive without local data storage or computational infrastructure requirements.


